questionAndAnswer01: Desert_1|A plant’s seeds stay buried, often for several years until it rains.|How do many plants survive in very hot and dry areas?|A plant’s seeds stay buried, often for several years until it rains.|The wind carries seeds to better conditions.|Seedlings sprout but stay buried until it rains.|They have roots that grow above ground to absorb nutrients from the air.|A plant’s roots can dry up but be rehydrated after it rains.

questionAndAnswerQuestion: How can islands come into existence?
questionAndAnswerCorrectAnswer: When volcanoes rise from the floor of the sea or when the water level rises or falls
questionAndAnswerResponse: When volcanoes rise from the floor of the sea or when the water level rises or falls
Islands_1: When volcanoes rise from the floor of the sea or when the water level rises or falls
questionAndAnswer01: Islands_1|When volcanoes rise from the floor of the sea or when the water level rises or falls|How can islands come into existence?|When tectonic plates collide and push land above sea level|When volcanoes rise from the floor of the sea or when the water level rises or falls|Only when underwater volcanoes erupt and form new land masses|Through the gradual erosion of coastal areas, separating land from the mainland|When ice sheets melt, exposing previously submerged land, the accumulation of sediment, or coral reefs

instructionForBlock:
In this block, you will use your cursor to track the center of a moving black cross until three letters appear, for example: Z R N. The letters will appear away from the cross, in the corner of your eye. They will flash quickly. After the letters disappear, you will report the MIDDLE letter you see (In the example above, the correct answer is "R"). The size of the letters and the spacing between the letters can vary greatly from trial to trial. In some trials, the letters might be very small. This experiment session is a continuation of the previous session of the experiment "Letter and Reading". It requires a computer with at least 6 cores.



In this session, you will perform tasks identical to what you did for the first one. You will respond to letters and read some texts.
instructionForBlock:
In this block, you will use your cursor to track the center of a moving black cross until three letters appear, for example: Z R N. The letters will appear away from the cross, in the corner of your eye. They will flash quickly. After the letters disappear, you will report the MIDDLE letter you see (In the example above, the correct answer is "R"). The size of the letters and the spacing between the letters can vary greatly from trial to trial. In some trials, the letters might be very small. Please try your best to keep your eyes on the cross at the center and view the letters with your side vision.

Click on PROCEED to continue.
instructionForResponse: What letter did you see in the center?
instructionForStimulus: Keep the cursor at the center of the black cross until the triplet appears.

instructionForBlock:
In this session, you will perform tasks on the computer.
In each task, when you answer correctly, you will hear a beep. Click on the "BEEP" button to make sure the computer's audio is on.

In this block, you must keep your cursor at the center of a black cross until a letter appears. While your cursor is at the center of the cross, please keep your eyes on the cross as well. The letter will appear away from the cross, in the corner of your eye. It will flash quickly. After the letter disappear, you will report the letter you see. The size of the letter can vary greatly from trial to trial. In some trials, the letter might be very small. Please try your best to keep your eyes on the cross at the center and view the letter with your side vision.

Click on PROCEED to continue.

In this session, you will perform tasks identical to what you did for the first one. You will respond to letters and read some texts.
instructionForBlock:
In this session, you will perform tasks on the computer.
In each task, when you answer correctly, you will hear a beep. Click on the "BEEP" button to make sure the computer's audio is on.

In this block, you must keep your cursor at the center of a black cross until a letter appears. While your cursor is at the center of the cross, please keep your eyes on the cross as well. The letter will appear away from the cross, in the corner of your eye. It will flash quickly. After the letter disappear, you will report the letter you see. The size of the letter can vary greatly from trial to trial. In some trials, the letter might be very small. Please try your best to keep your eyes on the cross at the center and view the letter with your side vision.

Click on PROCEED to continue.

_online2Description:
This experiment session is a continuation of the previous session of the experiment "Letter and Reading". It requires a computer with at least 6 cores.



In this session, you will perform tasks identical to what you did for the first one. You will respond to letters and read some texts.
instructionForBlock:
In this session, you will perform tasks on the computer.
In each task, when you answer correctly, you will hear a beep. Click on the "BEEP" button to make sure the computer's audio is on.

In this block, you must keep your cursor at the center of a black cross until a letter appears. While your cursor is at the center of the cross, please keep your eyes on the cross as well. The letter will appear away from the cross, in the corner of your eye. It will flash quickly. After the letter disappear, you will report the letter you see. The size of the letter can vary greatly from trial to trial. In some trials, the letter might be very small. Please try your best to keep your eyes on the cross at the center and view the letter with your side vision.

Click on PROCEED to continue.
instructionForResponse: What letter did you see?
instructionForStimulus: Keep the cursor at the center of the black cross until the letter appears.
